fields.title: Introduction to Django
fields.content:
In this lesson, we will learn what Django is and why it is used for building powerful web applications.
We will understand Djangos MVT architecture and how it handles requests and responses.
You will also learn the features of Django like ORM, admin panel, authentication, and security.
By the end of this lesson, you will have a clear idea of how Django works and what you can build using it.

fields.title: Django Project Setup
fields.content:
In this lesson, we will set up Django properly on our system.
We will create a virtual environment, install Django, and start a new Django project.
Then we will create a Django app and run the server to test the project in the browser.
You will also understand the purpose of important files like settings.py, urls.py, and manage.py.
By the end of this lesson, your Django project will be ready for building real modules and lessons.

fields.title: URLs and Views Basics
fields.content: In this lesson, we will learn how Django connects pages using URLs and Views. We will create a simple view function and link it in urls.py so it works in browser. By the end, you will understand URL routing and view mapping clearly.

fields.title: Models and Migrations
fields.content:
In this lesson, we will learn about Django Models and how they connect to the database.
We will create model classes, understand fields like CharField, IntegerField, DateTimeField, and relationships.
Then we will run makemigrations and migrate to create database tables.
By the end of this lesson, you will understand how Django stores data using models and migrations.

fields.title: Django Admin Panel
fields.content:
In this lesson, we will explore Django Admin Panel and how it makes managing data very easy.
We will create a superuser, login to /admin, and register models.
You will learn how to customize the admin view using list_display, search_fields, and ordering.
By the end of this lesson, you will be able to manage your project data through Django admin efficiently.

fields.title: CRUD Operations
fields.content:
In this lesson, we will learn CRUD operations (Create, Read, Update, Delete) in Django.
We will understand how to insert new data, show records from database, update existing records, and delete them.
You will also learn how Django ORM simplifies database queries.
By the end of this lesson, you will be able to build basic database functionality using Django.

fields.title: Templates and Static Files
fields.content:
In this lesson, we will learn how Django Templates work and how to display HTML pages dynamically.
We will understand template rendering using render() and how to pass data from views to templates.
Then we will learn how to configure and use static files like CSS, JavaScript, and images.
By the end of this lesson, you will be able to build professional-looking pages using templates and static files.

fields.title: Forms and Validation
fields.content:
In this lesson, we will learn how to create forms in Django and handle user input.
We will use Django forms to validate data and display form errors properly.
You will understand GET vs POST requests and how Django processes form submissions.
By the end of this lesson, you will be able to create forms for login, registration, and basic data collection with validation.

fields.title: Authentication (Login & Register)
fields.content:
In this lesson, we will learn how authentication works in Django.
We will create Register and Login functionality using Django authentication system.
You will understand how to protect pages using login_required and how sessions work.
By the end of this lesson, you will be able to build a secure login/register system for real applications.

fields.title: Python Introduction
fields.content:
In this lesson, we will understand what Python is and why it is one of the most popular programming languages.
We will learn where Python is used (web development, AI, automation, data science) and what makes it beginner-friendly.
You will also learn how Python code is executed and the importance of writing clean code.
By the end of this lesson, you will be ready to start writing basic Python programs.

fields.title: Variables and Data Types
fields.content:
In this lesson, we will learn what variables are and how to store data in Python.
We will explore data types like int, float, string, and boolean with simple examples.
You will also learn type conversion and how to check the type of a variable using type().
By the end of this lesson, you will be able to create variables and work with different kinds of data.

fields.title: If Else and Loops
fields.content:
In this lesson, we will learn decision making using if, elif, and else statements.
Then we will learn loops using for and while to repeat tasks and write efficient code.
You will understand break and continue statements and how to control loop execution.
By the end of this lesson, you will be able to write small programs using conditions and loops confidently.

fields.title: Python Functions
fields.content:
In this lesson, we will learn what functions are and why they are used.
We will create functions using def, pass arguments, and return values.
You will also understand the difference between parameters and arguments.
By the end, you will be able to write reusable Python functions confidently.

fields.title: Lists and Tuples
fields.content:
In this lesson, we will learn Python lists and tuples.
We will perform operations like indexing, slicing, adding, removing, and looping.
You will understand the difference between mutable (list) and immutable (tuple).
By the end, you can manage multiple values easily using lists and tuples.

fields.title: Dictionaries and Sets
fields.content:
In this lesson, we will learn dictionaries and sets in Python.
We will store key-value pairs using dict and access values easily.
You will learn common dictionary methods and set operations.
By the end, you can manage structured data using dictionaries and remove duplicates using sets.

fields.title: Object Oriented Programming (OOP)
fields.content:
In this lesson, we will learn the basics of Object Oriented Programming in Python.
We will understand class and object, and create a class with attributes and methods.
You will learn how OOP helps in organizing real-world applications.
By the end, you can build simple class-based programs in Python.

fields.title: Inheritance and Polymorphism
fields.content:
In this lesson, we will learn inheritance to reuse code between classes.
We will create parent and child classes and override methods.
You will also understand polymorphism and how Python supports it.
By the end, you can build advanced OOP structures using inheritance.

fields.title: Mini Project: Simple Calculator
fields.content:
In this lesson, we will build a mini project using Python basics.
We will create a calculator that performs addition, subtraction, multiplication, and division.
You will practice using functions, conditionals, loops, and user input.
By the end, you will have a working mini project and confidence to build more.
